Natividad Ychu Maza, 12 sept. 2006, San Lorenzo de Moxos
We are going to tell about a boy in his house.
vechjisoyre ma mperu te to mapeno ,
Vamos a contar de un chico en su casa,
And his parents, we don't know where they were.
ene no mueyano , wo vecha oypuka nowriko .
y de sus padres no sabemos donde estn (viven ?).
But we are going to see here, we are going to tell what happened to him (lit. what he underwent).
etotsero , vimoyre te pjoka , vechjisoyre to ... to makoyemgiene .
As vamos a mostrar, de esto vamos a contar lo que le pas.
The boy, in the room where he lives, at night, then.. he was with his dog.
ema , ma mperu , te to mawriko ptiku , to yoti , ene ... eto makochane to mayee paku .
El chico est en su cuarto, es la noche, y est acompaado de su perro.
There was also what must be a water container, it's probably from there that he drinks,
etjooi to tomuire towrikpuka to une , enepuka mueeo ,
haba tambien un recipiente con agua, possiblemente toma agua de ah,
And then... I am going to tell you what happened.
ene eto pjo ... to ... nechjisoyre to takoyemgienerii .
y de eso voy a contar lo que pas.
The boy, when he was sleeping, was with his dog.
ema mperu te timko , makochane to mayee paku .
El chico duerme acompaado de su perro,
y ese duerme con l tambien.
It supposedly was nighttime, he slept, he slept, and the frog entered the water container, in his room.
muechkresi to yoti , timkoripo , timkoripo ema , ene teetakoopo to uupe te to towriko to une , te to muemsrare .
cest peut-tre la nuit ADV.PRED GN.S
De repente es la noche, cuando l estaba durmiendo (2x), y la rana se meti donde haba agua, donde el duerme.
And when he woke up, it was probably already day-time, and his dog too, they got up.
ene ema te ... techrooopo tejamikpo , sachepopka , tomuire to mayee paku , ene ... techpukompo .
Cuando el se despert, ya de da, y su perro tambin, se levantaron.
He saw it, the frog had gone out of the water container.
muemopo ema , tyuchkopo eto to uupe te to towrare to une .
Lo vi l, sali la rana del agua.
It may have gone there, in his shoe.
Se habria metido en su sapato (la rana).
So he took his shoe to look if it was inside.
ene mavepo to maspatu , muemoyre to etjooinapuka tayee .
Saco su sapato para mirar si estaba all.
And his dog too searched the inside of the water container.
tomuire to mayee paku tatankopo te to tajue to towrare to une .
y su perro tambien bucaba al interior del recipiente de agua.
And put his head into it.
The boy was surprised that this has happened.
ma mperu maramignejcha to ene takeei .
El chico se sorprendi que eso hubiera pasado.
And the dog ran, he kept the water container on there (his head) in the bedroom (lit. the water container stayed), he had put his head into it.
ene tjunopopo eto to paku , tanosi to ... to ... towrare to une tayee te to ... muemsrare tkosiopsikwopo
daprs Calixta, il faut enlever tayee pour que ce soit correct.; tjnopopo
Y el perro corri, su cabeza en el recipiente de agua que estaba en su cuarto en qu habia metido su cabeza
And it (the dog) ran out. It was running with it (a pot on its head).
And outside, he bumped into the wall and it broke.
ene te to neko , tatupiokpo etopuka yuchmo , ene tewarakpo eto .
Y afuera se choc sera contra la pared, y se quebr.
He (the boy) went, he hugged his dog, he petted him because he had been scared that it (the jar) would stay (on the dog's head).
tyompo ema ene maviokpo to mayee paku muetsrarekpo jicho tyoyokrii te to tansi .
o dans maviokpo pourrait tre CLF 'o sans glottale
Se fue l (el chico) y le acareci su perro, lo acareci, tenia miedo que se quede (la jarra en su cabeza).
The dog of the boy saw the bee nest, high up.
to pona ... to mayee paku ma mperu taemopo eto to ... towo to moposiono , te to nuge .
to pona is perceived as a false start
Y su perro lo vi las abejas arriba. (hyp lit: el perro del chico lo vio, el lugar donde estaban las abejas, arriba).
And he (the boy) was looking at the hole (lit. house) of a rat.
ene ema muemorookooi to tapeno to kotso .
Y l (el chico) estaba mirando la cueva del ratn.
Will he come out or not?
And while he was watching, he watched the rat's dwelling, its house, it jumped and it looks like it hurt him on the nose.
ene to muemuirarii ema muemopo to towrare to kotso tapeno , tetereko kutimi ee ... tajracho te to masiri .
Mientras l estaba mirando donde vive el ratn, salt (el ratn) y parece que le hir (herir) algo en la nariz.
And his dog wanted to climb where the b... bees were (i.e. the bee nest).
ene eto to mayee paku tawooo topnucha eto to towriko to mopono ... moposiono .
Y su perro quera subir/trepar donde estn (viven ?) las abejas.
And it (the bee nest) went loose and fell on the ground, where the bees were living.
ene techmukpo eto tvnopo te poge , to towo to moposiono .
Se solt y cay en el suelo, donde viven (estan ?) las abejas (la colmena).
tomuire eto to kotso tyuchkopo tomuire .
What happened ? Did he get scared or frightened ? ( mettre en \fo Que le pas? Tendras miedo o asustado?)
A donde estara? Que se habra hecho? Tendras miedo o asustado?
And the dog's master, there he was, in the branches of a tree.
ene ema ma tkoye to paku , ene mawriko te to tatwogi to wkugi .
Pero el dueo del perro estaba en el gajo del arbol.
And there was a hole inside (the tree), he was looking at it.
Pero haba un hueco en el arbol, lo estaba mirando.
And from there an owl went out.
ene tayee tyuchkopo eto to yusa .
It must have been where she made her home.
It went out of there. And being scared, he fell on the floor (sparer la phrase en 2).
tyuchkopo tayee ene to mapisra ema tvenopopo te poge .
Sali de all y l de miedo se cay en el suelo.
And his dog was chasing the bees.
ene eto to mayee paku taponojokpo to ... to ... moposiono .
Y su perro de l lo correte las abejas.
And it went directly on the top of a round rock.
ene ene matupiru te to nuge mrisi .
Leo et Florencia confirment que cest "arriba de una piedra" et pas "en una piedra alta"
Y l se fue directo arriba de una piedra grande.
He did not see that it could be there was the antlers of the deer.
wo muema etjoripka to tatwoji tajiu to kjowo .
No lo vi el gajederio de las astas del ciervo.
The owl was also coming, as if it was chasing him, since he was afraid, he jumped from there and directly ended on the head of the deer.
takepripo to yusa tomuire kuti oni taponojokpooi to mapkosrawo ema teterekpo tayee , ene maretpiru te to tachuti to kjowo .
En eso vino la lechuza tambin como si lo hubiera correteado, l tuvo miedo y salt de all, y al saltar directo se cay en la cabeza del ciervo.
And then, his dog went also looking for him.
ene eto to mayee paku tomuire tatankopo .
Y de all su perro tambien lo busc.
And then, the deer ran, he carried him (the boy) on his head.
ene eto to tjunopopo to kjowo , tompo ema te to tachuti .
Cuando corri el ciervo, se lo llev a l en su cabeza.
His dog was following along also.
Y su perro tambin le sigui.
It went directly to the river gully, and threw him from there.
tatupiru te to tyuchusi kjokre ene tagopo tayee .
Se fue directo al barranco del rio y lo lanz de all.
It threw him into the water, and there was also his dog.
ema ... taewtsekpo , ene etopo tomuire to mayee paku .
Lo bot dentro del agua, y su perro tambin.
And he went out of it and his dog too.
ene tyuchkompo tayee tomuire to mayee paku .
Sali de all y su perro tambin.
He said (to his dog): "Don't bark!", he said, "Don't bark at all".
majichpo " wo ... wo ... wo pkupiooko " majichpo " pamtinachujcha ".
Le dijo (a su perro) : "no ladres", le dijo que se calle.
And they went to another tree and his dog was just staying with him.
ene tyonompo te to pona wkugi ene to mayee paku ta... tanosjiii mayee .
Y de all se fueron a otro arbol y su perro lo segui.
On the other side of the tree, the saw... he saw too two frogs.
te to pochkoyo te to wkugi naemopo ... mamuire muemopo eto to apina to uupiono .
j'entnds pas la glottale de 'po- et j'entends pu
En el otro lado del arbol vi l tambien dos ranas.
En el otro lado del arbol vieron... vi l tambien dos ranas.
Then the (the boy) seemingly wanted to catch the frogs.
ene ema mawooopka makootoka to uupiono .
Y l (el chico) quera agarrar las ranas.
And there in the river, the frogs jumped into the water.
ene enepo te to kjokre te to une tewtsaekwompo eto to uupiono .
Y en el rio dentras de agua se champaron las ranas.
They came from the tree, there they lived.
tyosono te to wkugi , ene towrikooi .
